What it Does
Added a blocklist where if you have a certain name you are blocked from ordering.

What it Demonstrates
if/else logic
basic control flow exit using exit() to halt anymore code
The difference between = and == in identifying variables and determing accuracy

What to Improve On
Menu Validation for determining a customer's order is actually available.
Input validation for if a customer types in the word three for example over the number 3.
Case Sensitivity for the blocklist.

Script

print("Hello, welcome to Zach's coffee shop!")


Menu = "\nBlack Coffee S/M/L/XL\nMacchiato S/M/L\nLondon Fog S/M/L\n"

CustomerName = input("What is your name?\n" )

if CustomerName == "Dan":
  print("Sorry, we can't serve you here.")
  exit()
else:
  print("\nHello " + CustomerName + ", thank you so much for coming in today! Here is our menu.\n" + Menu)
  
order = input("What can I get started for you " + CustomerName +"?\n")
print("\nYou got it " + CustomerName + ". ")

numberordered = input("How many would you like?\n")
price = 5
total = price * int(numberordered)

print("Your total is: $" + str(total) + "\n")

print("You got it. I will have your " + numberordered + " " + order + " right out in a few minutes!")
